<subSubSection id="62D6AA48A631B3F2C7CDE02E0DC6D233" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="7318A29E8A6802B3933C9F9440467475" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Habitat and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D897AB4429F5EBE0EA5013B0D48BCC4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Concentrated amongst rounded granitic boulders at 
<quantity id="5DBC17F2D30EDCB0EF44E9596A6AF9B5" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="0.5" unit="m" value="1100.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="500.0">500-1700 m</quantity>
alt. (
<bibRefCitation id="3EA4C23F60E367714E589B9C4DEFFCD0" author="Collenette, S" journalOrPublisher="National Commission for Wildlife Conservation and Development, Riyadh" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" refId="B15" refString="Collenette, S, 1999. Wildflowers of Saudi Arabia. National Commission for Wildlife Conservation and Development, Riyadh" title="Wildflowers of Saudi Arabia." year="1999">Collenette 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Flowering: March-April.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9ADFAD0C488635353F9C9BEE485BD052" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="54C7AFB4A5C4D575561F1B45BB5E61A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DCEDBFFD9F0F363A24531565BA39592B" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
The variety is most similar to the Ethiopian endemic 
<taxonomicName id="CA1A5E5927EDA6A3A28ADA2B393DDC83" authority="Bruyns, 2017 (R.Br.)" authorityName="M.G.Gilbert" authorityYear="1975" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="Huernia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Huernia boleana" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boleana">
<emphasis id="1C7EB4729F2B631BE595F759A400CF9A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Huernia boleana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be separated with flowers by the much more campanulate corolla that is wider than the long, pentagonal tube, the more conical papillae and the shorter inner coronal lobes (ca. 
<quantity id="8C951D1B303C13DAEBB1069A36A4ACCA" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
compared to ca. 
<quantity id="C28C0AE9403AEAA5505E380A87806751" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="C1D5A0416DAC7E9CD1E98FEF7D9CEEFC" genus="H." lsidName="H. boleana" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="boleana">
<emphasis id="C60D9099AAB20DA37236189136FD54AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">H. boleana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and with habit and habitat that is erect to decumbent amongst granitic rocks compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4B500000D208BA14CFB73D6727B8E1CE" genus="H." lsidName="H. boleana" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="boleana">
<emphasis id="E0A0C6B0CC93FF0259A15DD49203A15A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">H. boleana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is erect, pendulous or prostrate in basalt or sandstone.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87C6D9E4B1B3F8904786694B9D2400C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
It can be easily distinguished from the other varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="EE94F471B942E704B282511D6ED9709C" genus="C." lsidName="C. lodarensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="lodarensis">
<emphasis id="4EEB524EA3C9DAEDE6E8C4C97C85BAE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">C. lodarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed here by the stout branches, flowers with more evenly-rounded spots inside that are more red in colour and by the more slender papillae.
</paragraph>
